Pre-requisites
==============
1. GNU Make utility (optional)
2. gcc compiler (required)
3. GTK-2.0 library [libgtk2.0-dev] (required)
4. FFMPEG library [libavcodec-dev, libavformat-dev, libswscale-dev] (required)
5. Glade Interface Designer (optional)

Installation (on Ubuntu)
========================
1. Install GTK-2.0 library
    `sudo apt-get install libgtk2.0-dev`
2. Install FFMPEG library
    `sudo apt-get install libavcodec-dev libavformat-dev libswscale`
3. `cd` into project directory
4. Run `make clean` to remove any binaries if present
5. Run `make` to create new platform-dependant binaries
6. Execute `./sigextract` for the GUI version and `./sigextract_nogui` for the CUI version of the software

